[2] Nampula: bovine, serotype pending
Date: Mon 18 Jun 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(25) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26730


Foot-and-mouth disease, Mozambique
----------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 18 Jun 2018 from Dr Americo Da Conceicao, national director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Maputo, Mozambique.

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 17 May 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 May 2018
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Foot and mouth disease virus
Serotype: pending
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, clinical
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks, total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1(1/FMD/NPL): Namachepa, Namachepa, Mogovolas, Nampula
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 May 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1600 / 17 / 8 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Animals of different ages with excessive salivation, ulcerative lesions on the tongue, gums and interdigital space.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.06 / 0.50 / 47.06 / 0.50
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive, animals in transit

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, traceability, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Veterinary Research Institute (national laboratory) / Cattle / antibody detection ELISA / [not available] / Pending

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of
Namachepa, Mozambique: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5862351,64264

The European Commission for the Control of Foot-and-Mouth disease (FMD) monthly report "Global Foot-and-Mouth Disease Situation," January 2018 (see http://www.fao.org/fileadmin/user_upload/eufmd/FMD_reports_GMR/Jan_GMR_2018.pdf) notes that:

"A FMD outbreak, which occurred on 25 Dec 2017, was diagnosed on clinical basis in cattle of the village of Tchale B, Posto Adminstrative_Sede, Chicualacuala, Gaza. The affected area is located close to Gonorezoe National Park in Zimbabwe. Cattle of all ages were affected presenting salivation, lameness, and eruptive lesions in the mouth, on the tongue, and on the feet. The source of the outbreak is unknown and control measures adopted are movement control inside the country, surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, traceability, quarantine, and inactivation of the virus in products and by-products. Vaccination is permitted in case a suitable vaccine is available."

A summary table of the animals involved in that outbreak as well as a map with the location of the outbreak are available in the same report (page 25). - Mod.CRD]
